# Gemini — `.env` is read from this repo root (folder that contains `app/`), not from the shell cwd.
# Never commit real keys or paste them into chat/screenshots. If a key was exposed, revoke it in AI Studio and create a new one.
# HTTP 429 from narrative endpoints means Google accepted the key but quota is exhausted (or free-tier limit 0 for that model/project); wrong keys usually return 400 from Google, and a missing key returns our 400 `gemini_api_key_missing`.
GEMINI_API_KEY=
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
# If 429 persists, try another model id (separate quotas). `gemini-1.5-flash` often returns 404 on v1beta (retired/renamed).
# List names: curl.exe "https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models?key=YOUR_KEY"
# Examples that usually work: gemini-2.0-flash, gemini-2.5-flash, gemini-2.5-pro

# Default template language when request omits `locale` (`en`|`fa`).
# SN_REPORT_LOCALE=en

# Optional — other app settings use SN_ prefix
# SN_DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./data/surginote.db
